<exercise number="1"><statement><p>
    Make a table showing powers of <m>3</m> from <m>3^{−5}</m> to <m>3^5</m>. Illustrate why defining <m>3^0 = 1</m> makes sense.
</p></statement>
<answer><p>
    <tabular left="minor" right="minor" top="minor" bottom="minor" halign="center"><col right="major"/>
        <row>
            <cell><m>n</m></cell>
            <cell><m>-5</m></cell>
            <cell><m>-4</m></cell>
            <cell><m>-3</m></cell>
            <cell><m>-2</m></cell>
            <cell><m>-1</m></cell>
            <cell><m>0</m></cell>
            <cell><m>1</m></cell>
            <cell><m>2</m></cell>
            <cell><m>3</m></cell>
            <cell><m>4</m></cell>
            <cell><m>5</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><m>3^n</m></cell>
            <cell><m>\frac{1}{243} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\frac{1}{81} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\frac{1}{27} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\frac{1}{9} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>\frac{1}{3} </m></cell>
            <cell><m>1</m></cell>
            <cell><m>3</m></cell>
            <cell><m>9</m></cell>
            <cell><m>27</m></cell>
            <cell><m>81</m></cell>
            <cell><m>243</m></cell>
        </row>
    </tabular>
    Each time <m>n</m> increases by <m>1</m>, we multiply the power in the bottom row by <m>3</m>.
</p></answer>
</exercise>

<exercise number="2"><statement><p>
    Make a table showing powers of <m>5</m> from <m>5^{−4}</m> to <m>5^4</m>. Illustrate why defining <m>5^0 = 1</m> makes sense.
</p></statement></exercise>

<exercisegroup> 
    <introduction><p>
    Compute each power.
</p></introduction>

<exercise number="3"><statement><ol label="a" cols="4">
    <li><p><m>2^3</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>(-2)^3 </m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>2^{-3}</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>(-2)^{-3} </m></p></li>
</ol></statement>
<answer><ol label="a" cols="4">
    <li><p><m>8</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>-8</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>\dfrac{1}{8} </m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>\dfrac{-1}{8} </m></p></li>
</ol></answer>
</exercise>

